data.text:
Edwards-SmartOne ADDRESSABLE MONITOR MODULE

The SmartOne® Addressable Contact Input Device (AI) – an intelligent field device. With its microprocessor, memory, and electronics necessary. To interface N.O. or N.C. unpowered contacts to the FenwalNET control units. The electronics – contained in a high-impact polymer case, creating a small and durable device for installation.

Two types of AI’s – available. AI/NC for interfacing to normally closed devices and an AI/NO for interfacing to normally open devices. The AI may – located up to 2,500 feet from the monitored device with #18 AWG wiring.

FIELD PROGRAMMING

System address, owner location message, and reporting type – programmable via the compatible control unit configuration software program.

The System address is a 4-digit number that uniquely identifies each device. The owner location message is a 40-character, alphanumeric message that describes the location of the device.
